{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"queryExists"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","text":"CancellableRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil) -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that in many cases it is "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Time_of_check_to_time_of_use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and then execute something based on the outcome of that, because the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"file might have been created or removed in between the operations. The"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"general approach to handling that is to not check, but just do the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"operation and handle the errors as they come."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As an example of race-free checking, take the case of reading a file,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and if it doesn’t exist, creating it. There are two racy versions: read"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it, and on error create it; and: check if it exists, if not create it."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"These can both result in two processes creating the file (with perhaps"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a partially written file as the result). The correct approach is to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"always try to create the file with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_file_create()"},{"type":"text","text":" which will either"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"atomically create the file or fail with a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_IO_ERROR_EXISTS"},{"type":"text","text":" error."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"However, in many cases an existence check is useful in a user interface,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for instance to make a menu item sensitive\/insensitive, so that you don’t"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"have to fool users that something is possible and then just show an error"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"dialog. If you do this, you should make sure to also handle the errors"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that can happen due to races when you execute the operation."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/fileref\/queryexists(cancellable:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileRef\/queryExists(cancellable:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Utility function to check if a particular file exists. This is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"implemented using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_file_query_info()"},{"type":"text","text":" and as such does blocking I\/O."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"role":"symbol","title":"queryExists(cancellable:)","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"queryExists"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:3GIO12FileProtocolPAAE11queryExists11cancellableSbAA14CancellableRefVSg_tF::SYNTHESIZED::s:3GIO7FileRefV","extendedModule":"GIO","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileRef","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileRef\/FileProtocol-Implementations"]]},"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/CancellableRef":{"role":"symbol","title":"CancellableRef","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"CancellableRef"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"GCancellable is a thread-safe operation cancellation stack used"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"throughout GIO to allow for cancellation of synchronous and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"asynchronous operations."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"CancellableRef"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/cancellableref"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"role":"collection","title":"GIO","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/FileRef/FileProtocol-Implementations":{"role":"collectionGroup","title":"FileProtocol Implementations","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileRef\/FileProtocol-Implementations","kind":"article","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/fileref\/fileprotocol-implementations"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/FileRef/queryExists(cancellable:)":{"role":"symbol","title":"queryExists(cancellable:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"queryExists"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Utility function to check if a particular file exists. This is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"implemented using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_file_query_info()"},{"type":"text","text":" and as such does blocking I\/O."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileRef\/queryExists(cancellable:)","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/fileref\/queryexists(cancellable:)"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/FileRef":{"role":"symbol","title":"FileRef","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"FileRef"}],"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GFile"},{"type":"text","text":" is a high level abstraction for manipulating files on a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"virtual file system. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GFiles"},{"type":"text","text":" are lightweight, immutable objects"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that do no I\/O upon creation. It is necessary to understand that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GFile"},{"type":"text","text":" objects do not represent files, merely an identifier for a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"file. All file content I\/O is implemented as streaming operations"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(see "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GInputStream"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GOutputStream"},{"type":"text","text":")."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileRef","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"FileRef"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/fileref"},"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Time_of_check_to_time_of_use":{"title":"racy to first check for file existence","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"racy to first check for file existence"}],"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Time_of_check_to_time_of_use","url":"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Time_of_check_to_time_of_use"}}}